List<Map<String, dynamic>> privacy1Policy = [
  {
    "text1":
        """\nWe firmly believe that trust is key for developing successful and lasting relationships. In this respect, the protection of your personal data and privacy is no exception.
This is the reason why Bursa puts great emphasis on collecting and processing your personal data with utmost care and in compliance with the applicable legal framework.
In order to inform you in the most transparent manner, Bursa has prepared the privacy policy below, which explains in detail why and how your personal data are processed where you browse this website.""",
    "text2":
        """\nThis privacy policy (hereinafter the “Privacy Policy”) is intended to inform you, as a user of the Bursa website www.wearebursa.com (hereinafter the “the website”), about the way Capital Management Group(hereinafter “Bursa”) processes, as controller, your personal information (hereinafter “Personal Data”) enabling Bursa to identify you either directly or indirectly  in the context of your use of the Website.""",
    "text3":
        """\nWhere you use the Website, Bursa processes your Personal Data for various purposes, each of them being duly legitimated by a valid legal basis.
First, Bursa collects and processes your Personal Data for managing and following up any questions and/or requests you may submit. As such, please note that this processing is only carried out in the event you submit a question and/or request. Otherwise, your Personal Data are not processed for this purpose.
This processing requires that Bursa collect and process the following categories of Personal Data: 
    (i) identification data (i.e., your first name, your last name, and your contact details); 
    (ii) data related to your professional life (i.e., the identity of your employer and your job position); and 
    (iii) the content of the message(s) you sent to Bursa as part of your question/request.
While processing your Personal Data for this purpose, Bursa relies on its legitimate interest, which consists in duly managing its relationships with you.
Second, if you are an investor, you may have been granted by Bursa an investor account enabling you to access specific pages and contents through the Website.
For managing your investor account, and notably ensuring that you are entitled to access contents dedicated to investors only, Bursa needs to process and collect your identification data (i.e., your first name, your last name, your contact details as well as your login and password for accessing your investor account) as well as data related to your professional life (i.e. the identity of your employer). The legal basis of this processing is the necessity for Bursa to perform a contract to which you are a party.
Third, if you are willing to subscribe to its newsletter, Bursa needs to collect and process your email address, which is a Personal Data, in order to properly manage your subscription.
Please note however that Bursa will only send you its newsletter and process your email address accordingly provided it has obtained your prior consent, which constitutes the legal basis of this processing.
Lastly, as Bursa is willing to understand how users interact with its Website, it needs to process various browsing information resulting from cookies which qualify as Personal Data. Thus, the fourth category of processing Bursa carries out with your Personal Data is the performance of analytic operation related to the Website traffic and use.
In this respect, the legal basis Bursa relies upon is its legitimate interest which consists in: 
    (i) better understanding the way its Website is browsed by users (including you); and 
(ii) improving the Website where needed.
In any event, and disregarding the processing purpose at stake, please note that Bursa will comply with a strict data minimisation principle and will thus only collect and process Personal Data which is necessary for the above purposes.
Besides, for managing your questions/requests, your investor account as well as your subscription to the newsletter, the provision of your Personal Data is a contractual requirement. In this respect, sharing your Personal Data with Bursa is thus mandatory, otherwise Bursa will not be able to: 
    (i) address your questions/requests; 
    (ii) manage your investor account (including to give you access to content specifically dedicated to investors); and/or 
    (iii) send you its newsletter.""",
    "text4":
        """\nBursa shares your Personal Data with third-party service providers and suppliers which assist Bursa for fulfilling the purposes specified in this Privacy Policy.
For example, to manage your investor account, Bursa relies on the services of Intralinks, Inc., which notably administers the portal through which you can log in. Thus, Intralinks accesses your Personal Data, notably your login and password.
Another example is to be found with respect to cookies. Indeed, to perform the analytic operations regarding your use of the Website, Bursa relies on the services of Google LLC, which thus access and processes your Personal Data resulting from the use of cookies.
To the extent this is necessary, Bursa also communicates your Personal Data to other entities of the Bursa group (e.g., the question you submitted to Bursa actually concerns another entity of the Bursa group and the latter will thus contact you directly to answer your question if relevant).
Furthermore, as the case may be, Bursa shares your Personal Data with competent courts and any other governmental and/or public authorities requesting access to your Personal Data, within the extent legally permitted.
In any event, Bursa communicates your Personal Data to the above recipients on a strict need-to-know basis and only as necessary for fulfilling duly identified processing purposes.""",
    "text5":
        """\nPlease note that, as part of the processing implemented for managing your investor account and performing analytic operations, Bursa transfers your Personal Data to Google LLC., which is located outside the European Economic Area (“EEA”), in the United States of America. Bursa may also need to transfer your Personal Data to other entities of the Bursa Group. Please note that some of these are located outside the EEA in countries that are not regarded by the European Commission (“EC”) as providing an adequate level of protection to Personal Data (e.g., China, Singapore, USA).
For transfers of your Personal Data to such countries, Bursa has implemented appropriate safeguards approved by the EC. This includes Binding Corporate Rules (“BCR”) between the various entities of the Bursa group or entering into Standard Contractual Clauses with the recipients of the Personal Data.""",
    "text6":
        """\nBursa only retains your Personal Data for a retention period not exceeding what is necessary in light of the processing purpose at stake. As a result, the data retention period implemented by Bursa depends upon the processing purpose as detailed below.
First, with respect to the management of your questions and/or requests, Bursa will not retain your Personal Data for more than five (5) years following the last contact on your initiative.
Second, regarding the management of your investor account, Bursa will retain your Personal Data until your investor account is closed. Nevertheless, if Bursa needs to retain your Personal Data for evidence purpose beyond the date your investor account is closed, the maximum retention period applicable will then be in line with the statute of limitation and will not exceed the period during which Bursa is required to retain evidence.”
Third, where Bursa processes your Personal Data for managing your subscription to its newsletter, your Personal Data will be retained by Bursa until you unsubscribe from the newsletter.
Lastly, the Personal Data processed by Bursa or on its behalf for performing analytic operations shall not be retained by Bursa after the analytic operations are finalized and the corresponding reports/summaries are completed.
Where the applicable retention period expires, Bursa either deletes your Personal Data or irrevocably anonymises it so that you can no longer be identified.
Where Bursa considers it does not need to retain your Personal Data in its active database, it will archive it and will ensure that access thereto is restricted to a limited number of persons who have an actual need to access your Personal Data.""",
    "text7":
        """\nAs a data subject, you benefit from various rights regarding the processing of your Personal Data. These are as follows:
    (i) right to request from Bursa access to and rectification or erasure of your Personal Data;
    (ii) right to request from Bursa restriction of the processing concerning you;
    (iii) right to object to the processing of your Personal Data;
